From Kilpatrick and Bressloff 2010 \[\begin{align*} \mu u_t &= -u + \int_{-\infty}^\infty w(x,x^\prime) q(x^\prime,t) f( u(x^\prime,t) - a(x^\prime,t)) \ dx^\prime \\ q_t &= \frac{1 - q}{\alpha} - \beta q f(u - a) \\ \epsilon a_t &= -a + \gamma f(u - a) \end{align*}\]

xs = np.linspace(a,b,n)
h = xs[1]-xs[0]

def firing_rate(u):
    return np.heaviside(u-Î¸, .5)
    
M = .5*np.exp( - np.abs( np.subtract.outer(xs, xs) ) ) * h

def convolution(u):
    return M@firing_rate(u)

def RK4_step(F, t, u, dt):
    k1 = F(t,u)
    k2 = F(t+dt/2, u + dt/2*k1)
    k3 = F(t+dt/2, u + dt/2*k2)
    k4 = F(t+dt, u + dt*k3)
    return u + dt/6*(k1+2*k2+2*k3+k4)

# u is a vector [u, q, a]
# F = lambda t, u: np.array([
#         1/Î¼ * (-u[0] + M@(u[1]*firing_rate(u[0]) - u[2])),
#         (1-u[1])/Î± - Î²*u[1]*firing_rate(u[0]-u[2]),
#         (-u[2] + Î³*firing_rate(u[0]-u[2]))/Ïµ
#     ])
def F(t,u):
    temp = firing_rate(u[0] - u[2])
    ret = np.array([
        1/Î¼ * (-u[0] + M@(u[1]*temp)),
        (1-u[1])/Î± - Î²*u[1]*temp,
        (-u[2] + Î³*temp)/Ïµ
    ])
    return ret
def cos_bell(x, center=0, width=2*np.pi, height=1):
    return (np.cos((x-center)/width*2*np.pi)+1)/2*height * np.heaviside(x-center+width/2,0) * np.heaviside(-x+center+width/2,0)
